label: Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported
definition: The data are available under the Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported Public License (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/).

label: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
definition: The data are available under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International Public License (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/).

label: collection cost charge
definition: A charge is made related to the cost of collecting the data.

label: commercial charge
definition: A charge significantly exceeding the cost of data collection and delivery is made for usage of the data.

label: licence
definition: Conditions of supply and usage of the data are specified in a formal agreement.

label: SeaDataNet licence
definition: Access to the data and usage are as specified in the SeaDataNet data policy and licence agreement

label: moratorium
definition: Data are initially restricted, but the access condition relaxes to academic or unrestricted once a specified period of time after an event (such as collection, publication, completion of QC procedures or project cessation) has elapsed.

label: no access
definition: Access to the data cannot be negotiated.

label: distribution cost charge
definition: A charge is made to cover the costs of delivering data to the user.

label: organisation
definition: The data are unrestricted to members of an organisation or a virtual organisation (such as project or cruise participants) but restricted to anybody else.

label: by negotiation
definition: The data are witheld from general circulation and disclosure but access may be obtained on a case-by-case basis through negotiation.

label: academic
definition: The data are freely available for research and education purposes.  Usage acknowledgement is usually expected.

label: unknown
definition: The correct value is not known to and not computable by the creator of this information. However a correct value probably exists.

label: unrestricted
definition: The data are freely available to anybody and may be used for any purpose. Usage acknowledgement may be required.
